      it if it doesnt exist.
    - Start ec2-set-apt-sources at first bootup.
  * debian/rules:
    - Install ec2-set-apt-sources.
  * debian/control:
    - Add python-configobj as a dependency.
  * debian/{install,dirs}
    - Create an /etc/ec2-init to read the configuration file and install it.

